hitro
------------------------------------------
Markov chain sampler based on the HIT-and-run algorithm combined with the
Ratio-Of-uniforms method.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libhitro-devel-1.0-1bl3
  libhitro0-1.0-1bl3
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://statmath.wu.ac.at/software/hitro/

Canonical download:
  https://statmath.wu.ac.at/software/hitro/hitro-1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack hitro-1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./hitro-1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/hitro-1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/hitro-1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libhitro0-1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libhitro-devel-1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(hitro)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/hitro.README
  /usr/share/doc/hitro/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/hitro/README

(libhitro0)
  /usr/bin/cyghitro-0.dll

(libhitro-devel)
  /usr/include/hitro.h
  /usr/lib/libhitro.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/hitro.pc

------------------

Port Notes:

